SWINE FEVER/HOG CHOLERA - BELGIUM (03)
**************************************
Date: Fri, 18 Jul 1997 13:57:09 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@usa.healthnet.org>
Via: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
[see
Swine fever/Hog Cholera - Belgium 970703141911
Swine fever/Hog Cholera - Belgium (02) 970707152102]
Source: Translation of a fax received on 11 July 1997 from Dr L. Hallet,
Counsellor General, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Brussels.
End of previous report period: 8 July 1997. End of this report period: 11
July 1997.
New outbreak:
Location: Bocholt Municipality, Limburg province
No. of outbreaks: 1
Total number of outbreaks identified since 1 January 1997: seven (7)
Description of affected population in the new outbreak: mixed stock
Total number of animals in the new outbreak:

susceptible 1,153
cases ...
deaths ...
destroyed 1,153
slaughtered ...

Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Veterinary Research
Institute (INRV).
B. Diagnostic tests used: virus isolation; direct immunofluorescence.
C. Causal agent: classical swine fever virus; typing in progress.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: investigations under way.
B. Mode of spread: epidemiological survey in progress.
C. Other epidemiological details: outbreak detected following analysis of
samples from pigs subjected to preventive slaughter (in-contact farm).
Control measures during reporting period: stamping out; quarantine measures
and movement control inside the country; vaccination prohibited; control
programme covering the entire country.
